    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im building this new fintech startup and i'm trying to get the hiring process right from the start. our core team is pretty small right now—just a few high-achieving, very similar people who vibe really well together. i want to make sure that as we scale, we don't lose that energy. can you help me come up with some interview questions to see if a candidate is actually a good 'culture fit' and will blend in seamlessly with a team like ours?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since your current team already knows each other intimately, the best approach is to ask candidates to describe how they navigated early-stage challenges in previous roles where close collaboration was essential. This helps reveal their communication style and whether they thrive in tight-knit environments. You can also include a scenario question about a past conflict or disagreement, asking them to explain how they resolved it while respecting teammates' perspectives and maintaining team momentum. Finally, having a current founder or senior member role-play a time-sensitive problem will show if the candidate naturally aligns with your core team's high-achieving energy.",
